# Agent Context (CLAUDE.md) - Go stack

> This repo applies the [Excellence Standards - Engineering (ESE)](.standards/STANDARDS.md). These instructions apply to any AI coding agent working in this repository.

## Bootstrap

Run the bootstrap script before any other work if this project has unfilled ESE placeholders. See the canonical AGENTS.md / CLAUDE.md for the full bootstrap check and procedure.

## Stack-specific commands

**Test runner.** Before declaring a feature complete, run:

```
go test ./...
```

For a tighter loop:

```
go test -run <TestName> ./<pkg>
```

For race detection and coverage:

```
go test -race -cover ./...
```

**Lint.** This project uses `golangci-lint` (replace with `staticcheck` / `go vet` if different):

```
golangci-lint run ./...
```

Plus the always-present vet:

```
go vet ./...
```

**Format.** `gofmt` is non-negotiable:

```
gofmt -l -s -d .
```

`goimports` for import ordering:

```
goimports -l -d .
```

**Build.** Binary build:

```
go build ./...
```

**Pre-commit.** Install the hook once per clone:

```
ln -sf ../../scripts/pre-commit .git/hooks/pre-commit
```

## Go-specific ESE notes

- Follow standard Go conventions: effective Go, idiomatic error handling, no panics in library code.
- Module pinning via `go.mod` + `go.sum`; run `go mod tidy` before commit.
- Internal packages under `internal/` for non-exportable code; do not rely on lowercase names alone.
- Error wrapping with `fmt.Errorf("...%w", err)` so errors retain their chain.
- Vulnerability scan via `govulncheck`:

```
govulncheck ./...
```

- Secrets must not land in source; use env vars or a secret manager. `.env.example` checked in; `.env` gitignored.

## Universal ESE rules

The full set of ESE rules that apply to every project (artifact scaffolding, writing standards, commit discipline, release discipline, submodule upgrades) live in the canonical [AGENTS.md](.standards/starters/AGENTS.md) at `.standards/starters/AGENTS.md`. Read that file for cross-stack rules. This CLAUDE.md supplements it with Go-specific commands.
